1. login as root cd ~/.ssh
2. ssh -i id_rsa admin@public_ip_master
3. kubectl get nodes
4. kubectl get pods
5. To create a pod  
   => kubectl run sample-nginx --image=nginx --replicas=2 --port=80 
   =>             (pod name )    (docker image) (no of replicas) (export port)

6. kubectl get deployments
7. kubectl get services //
8.  To create a service to access created container 
     => kubectl expose deployment sample-nginx --port=80 --type=LoadBalancer
9. kubectl get services
10 kubectl get pods
11. kubectl describe pod pod_id      
